scopecontent.p:
This series contains professional correspondence, publishing contracts, book proposals, drafts, page proofs, cover art, royalties, publicity files, and other materials generated during Burton's career in publishing, particularly as an editor at Gay Men's Press and Millivres Books. Gay British authors represented include Roger Baker (
                     Drag: A History of Female Impersonation in the Performing Arts
                  ), Francis King (
                     Yesterday Came Suddenly
                  ), and Robin Maugham, with whom Burton worked as an assistant. There are also drafts by Canadian writer Ian Young.
